{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":435,"text":"All right. So, like all good stories,"},{"time":2418,"text":"this starts a long, long time ago"},{"time":4352,"text":"when there was basically nothing."},{"time":6501,"text":"So here is a complete picture of the universe"},{"time":8901,"text":"about 14-odd billion years ago."},{"time":12353,"text":"All energy is concentrated into a single point of energy."},{"time":15437,"text":"For some reason it explodes,"},{"time":17021,"text":"and you begin to get these things."},{"time":19137,"text":"So you're now about 14 billion years into this."},{"time":22003,"text":"And these things expand and expand and expand"},{"time":23899,"text":"into these giant galaxies,"},{"time":25598,"text":"and you get trillions of them."},{"time":26917,"text":"And within these galaxies"},{"time":29065,"text":"you get these enormous dust clouds."},{"time":31184,"text":"And I want you to pay particular attention"},{"time":32949,"text":"to the three little prongs"}]},{"cues":[{"time":34399,"text":"in the center of this picture."},{"time":36300,"text":"If you take a close-up of those,"},{"time":37715,"text":"they look like this."},{"time":39368,"text":"And what you're looking at is columns of dust"},{"time":42218,"text":"where there's so much dust --"},{"time":44265,"text":"by the way, the scale of this is a trillion vertical miles --"},{"time":48598,"text":"and what's happening is there's so much dust,"},{"time":51516,"text":"it comes together and it fuses"},{"time":53450,"text":"and ignites a thermonuclear reaction."},{"time":56909,"text":"And so what you're watching"},{"time":57751,"text":"is the birth of stars."},{"time":59736,"text":"These are stars being born out of here."},{"time":61393,"text":"When enough stars come out,"},{"time":63861,"text":"they create a galaxy."},{"time":65659,"text":"This one happens to be a particularly important galaxy,"},{"time":69093,"text":"because you are here."},{"time":71309,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":72476,"text":"And as you take a close-up of this galaxy,"},{"time":74127,"text":"you find a relatively normal,"},{"time":76192,"text":"not particularly interesting star."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78560,"text":"By the way, you're now about two-thirds of the way into this story."},{"time":82575,"text":"So this star doesn't even appear"},{"time":84757,"text":"until about two-thirds of the way into this story."},{"time":87708,"text":"And then what happens"},{"time":88786,"text":"is there's enough dust left over"},{"time":90192,"text":"that it doesn't ignite into a star,"},{"time":92158,"text":"it becomes a planet."},{"time":94158,"text":"And this is about a little over four billion years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98983,"text":"And soon thereafter"},{"time":100416,"text":"there's enough material left over"},{"time":102333,"text":"that you get a primordial soup,"},{"time":106896,"text":"and that creates life."},{"time":108660,"text":"And life starts to expand and expand and expand,"},{"time":112541,"text":"until it goes kaput."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114292,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":117780,"text":"Now the really strange thing"},{"time":119210,"text":"is life goes kaput, not once, not twice,"},{"time":122116,"text":"but five times."},{"time":124332,"text":"So almost all life on Earth"},{"time":126434,"text":"is wiped out about five times."},{"time":128898,"text":"And as you're thinking about that,"},{"time":130450,"text":"what happens is you get more and more complexity,"},{"time":132882,"text":"more and more stuff"},{"time":134116,"text":"to build new things with."},{"time":138234,"text":"And we don't appear"},{"time":139504,"text":"until about 99.96 percent of the time into this story,"},{"time":145152,"text":"just to put ourselves and our ancestors in perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149082,"text":"So within that context, there's two theories of the case"},{"time":152541,"text":"as to why we're all here."},{"time":154230,"text":"The first theory of the case"},{"time":155819,"text":"is that's all she wrote."},{"time":159228,"text":"Under that theory,"},{"time":160587,"text":"we are the be-all and end-all"},{"time":162423,"text":"of all creation."},{"time":164156,"text":"And the reason for trillions of galaxies,"},{"time":167040,"text":"sextillions of planets,"},{"time":169053,"text":"is to create something that looks like that"},{"time":173763,"text":"and something that looks like that."},{"time":177396,"text":"And that's the purpose of the universe;"},{"time":178937,"text":"and then it flat-lines,"},{"time":180221,"text":"it doesn't get any better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181532,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":186012,"text":"The only question you might want to ask yourself is,"},{"time":188831,"text":"could that be just mildly arrogant?"},{"time":194066,"text":"And if it is --"},{"time":195807,"text":"and particularly given the fact that we came very close to extinction."},{"time":201189,"text":"There were only about 2,000 of our species left."},{"time":204556,"text":"A few more weeks without rain,"},{"time":206639,"text":"we would have never seen any of these."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209723,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":216422,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":221056,"text":"So maybe you have to think about a second theory"},{"time":224022,"text":"if the first one isn't good enough."},{"time":226939,"text":"Second theory is: Could we upgrade?"},{"time":228723,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":231622,"text":"Well, why would one ask a question like that?"},{"time":234856,"text":"Because there have been at least 29 upgrades so far"},{"time":237321,"text":"of humanoids."},{"time":239357,"text":"So it turns out that we have upgraded."},{"time":242207,"text":"We've upgraded time and again and again."},{"time":244122,"text":"And it turns out that we keep discovering upgrades."},{"time":247038,"text":"We found this one last year."},{"time":249222,"text":"We found another one last month."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251839,"text":"And as you're thinking about this,"},{"time":254038,"text":"you might also ask the question:"},{"time":256141,"text":"So why a single human species?"},{"time":259238,"text":"Wouldn't it be really odd"},{"time":261072,"text":"if you went to Africa and Asia and Antarctica"},{"time":264856,"text":"and found exactly the same bird --"},{"time":267475,"text":"particularly given that we co-existed at the same time"},{"time":271267,"text":"with at least eight other versions of humanoid"},{"time":274053,"text":"at the same time on this planet?"},{"time":276521,"text":"So the normal state of affairs"},{"time":278400,"text":"is not to have just a Homo sapiens;"},{"time":280910,"text":"the normal state of affairs"},{"time":281931,"text":"is to have various versions of humans walking around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285760,"text":"And if that is the normal state of affairs,"},{"time":288577,"text":"then you might ask yourself,"},{"time":290945,"text":"all right, so if we want to create something else,"},{"time":293010,"text":"how big does a mutation have to be?"},{"time":295878,"text":"Well Svante Paabo has the answer."},{"time":298510,"text":"The difference between humans and Neanderthal"},{"time":301310,"text":"is 0.004 percent of gene code."},{"time":304609,"text":"That's how big the difference is"},{"time":306309,"text":"one species to another."},{"time":308526,"text":"This explains most contemporary political debates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312926,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":314861,"text":"But as you're thinking about this,"},{"time":318072,"text":"one of the interesting things"},{"time":319430,"text":"is how small these mutations are and where they take place."},{"time":322827,"text":"Difference human/Neanderthal"},{"time":324160,"text":"is sperm and testis,"},{"time":325893,"text":"smell and skin."},{"time":327261,"text":"And those are the specific genes"},{"time":328747,"text":"that differ from one to the other."},{"time":331427,"text":"So very small changes can have a big impact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334528,"text":"And as you're thinking about this,"},{"time":336160,"text":"we're continuing to mutate."},{"time":338676,"text":"So about 10,000 years ago by the Black Sea,"},{"time":341577,"text":"we had one mutation in one gene"},{"time":343637,"text":"which led to blue eyes."},{"time":346193,"text":"And this is continuing and continuing and continuing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350077,"text":"And as it continues,"},{"time":351511,"text":"one of the things that's going to happen this year"},{"time":353276,"text":"is we're going to discover the first 10,000 human genomes,"},{"time":356609,"text":"because it's gotten cheap enough to do the gene sequencing."},{"time":359878,"text":"And when we find these,"},{"time":361466,"text":"we may find differences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363960,"text":"And by the way, this is not a debate that we're ready for,"},{"time":367036,"text":"because we have really misused the science in this."},{"time":370412,"text":"In the 1920s, we thought there were major differences between people."},{"time":374095,"text":"That was partly based on Francis Galton's work."},{"time":377893,"text":"He was Darwin's cousin."},{"time":380029,"text":"But the U.S., the Carnegie Institute,"},{"time":382344,"text":"Stanford, American Neurological Association"},{"time":384926,"text":"took this really far."},{"time":386794,"text":"That got exported and was really misused."},{"time":390393,"text":"In fact, it led to some absolutely horrendous"},{"time":393078,"text":"treatment of human beings."},{"time":395091,"text":"So since the 1940s, we've been saying there are no differences,"},{"time":397685,"text":"we're all identical."},{"time":399005,"text":"We're going to know at year end if that is true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402282,"text":"And as we think about that,"},{"time":404014,"text":"we're actually beginning to find things"},{"time":405532,"text":"like, do you have an ACE gene?"},{"time":408998,"text":"Why would that matter?"},{"time":410976,"text":"Because nobody's ever climbed an 8,000-meter peak without oxygen"},{"time":415014,"text":"that doesn't have an ACE gene."},{"time":417764,"text":"And if you want to get more specific,"},{"time":419633,"text":"how about a 577R genotype?"},{"time":422648,"text":"Well it turns out that every male Olympic power athelete ever tested"},{"time":427348,"text":"carries at least one of these variants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430598,"text":"If that is true,"},{"time":432252,"text":"it leads to some very complicated questions"},{"time":434410,"text":"for the London Olympics."},{"time":436211,"text":"Three options:"},{"time":437730,"text":"Do you want the Olympics to be a showcase"},{"time":440562,"text":"for really hardworking mutants?"},{"time":443262,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":444995,"text":"Option number two:"},{"time":447730,"text":"Why don't we play it like golf or sailing?"},{"time":451128,"text":"Because you have one and you don't have one,"},{"time":453602,"text":"I'll give you a tenth of a second head start."},{"time":457597,"text":"Version number three:"},{"time":458668,"text":"Because this is a naturally occurring gene"},{"time":460737,"text":"and you've got it and you didn't pick the right parents,"},{"time":463519,"text":"you get the right to upgrade."},{"time":467468,"text":"Three different options."},{"time":469219,"text":"If these differences are the difference"},{"time":470841,"text":"between an Olympic medal and a non-Olympic medal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474219,"text":"And it turns out that as we discover these things,"},{"time":477053,"text":"we human beings really like to change"},{"time":480388,"text":"how we look, how we act,"},{"time":482082,"text":"what our bodies do."},{"time":483676,"text":"And we had about 10.2 million plastic surgeries in the United States,"},{"time":488050,"text":"except that with the technologies that are coming online today,"},{"time":491367,"text":"today's corrections, deletions,"},{"time":494068,"text":"augmentations and enhancements"},{"time":495987,"text":"are going to seem like child's play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498900,"text":"You already saw the work by Tony Atala on TED,"},{"time":502601,"text":"but this ability to start filling"},{"time":506168,"text":"things like inkjet cartridges with cells"},{"time":509101,"text":"are allowing us to print skin, organs"},{"time":513775,"text":"and a whole series of other body parts."},{"time":516525,"text":"And as these technologies go forward,"},{"time":518409,"text":"you keep seeing this, you keep seeing this, you keep seeing things --"},{"time":522193,"text":"2000, human genome sequence --"},{"time":524967,"text":"and it seems like nothing's happening,"},{"time":528749,"text":"until it does."},{"time":531861,"text":"And we may just be in some of these weeks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535385,"text":"And as you're thinking about"},{"time":536984,"text":"these two guys sequencing a human genome in 2000"},{"time":540435,"text":"and the Public Project sequencing the human genome in 2000,"},{"time":543988,"text":"then you don't hear a lot,"},{"time":547152,"text":"until you hear about an experiment last year in China,"},{"time":551136,"text":"where they take skin cells from this mouse,"},{"time":555153,"text":"put four chemicals on it,"},{"time":556886,"text":"turn those skin cells into stem cells,"},{"time":560452,"text":"let the stem cells grow"},{"time":561917,"text":"and create a full copy of that mouse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565004,"text":"That's a big deal."},{"time":568251,"text":"Because in essence"},{"time":569267,"text":"what it means is you can take a cell,"},{"time":571415,"text":"which is a pluripotent stem cell,"},{"time":573701,"text":"which is like a skier at the top of a mountain,"},{"time":576385,"text":"and those two skiers become two pluripotent stem cells,"},{"time":580202,"text":"four, eight, 16,"},{"time":581984,"text":"and then it gets so crowded"},{"time":583652,"text":"after 16 divisions"},{"time":585452,"text":"that those cells have to differentiate."},{"time":587954,"text":"So they go down one side of the mountain,"},{"time":589387,"text":"they go down another."},{"time":590620,"text":"And as they pick that,"},{"time":592154,"text":"these become bone,"},{"time":594404,"text":"and then they pick another road and these become platelets,"},{"time":597336,"text":"and these become macrophages,"},{"time":599453,"text":"and these become T cells."},{"time":600720,"text":"But it's really hard, once you ski down,"},{"time":602672,"text":"to get back up."},{"time":604195,"text":"Unless, of course, if you have a ski lift."},{"time":609607,"text":"And what those four chemicals do"},{"time":612056,"text":"is they take any cell"},{"time":614125,"text":"and take it way back up the mountain"},{"time":616057,"text":"so it can become any body part."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618090,"text":"And as you think of that,"},{"time":619818,"text":"what it means is potentially"},{"time":621798,"text":"you can rebuild a full copy"},{"time":623973,"text":"of any organism"},{"time":625840,"text":"out of any one of its cells."},{"time":628426,"text":"That turns out to be a big deal"},{"time":630957,"text":"because now you can take, not just mouse cells,"},{"time":633523,"text":"but you can human skin cells"},{"time":635841,"text":"and turn them into human stem cells."},{"time":639491,"text":"And then what they did in October"},{"time":642689,"text":"is they took skin cells, turned them into stem cells"},{"time":646089,"text":"and began to turn them into liver cells."},{"time":649762,"text":"So in theory,"},{"time":650806,"text":"you could grow any organ from any one of your cells."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655990,"text":"Here's a second experiment:"},{"time":657708,"text":"If you could photocopy your body,"},{"time":660841,"text":"maybe you also want to take your mind."},{"time":663893,"text":"And one of the things you saw at TED"},{"time":665458,"text":"about a year and a half ago"},{"time":666708,"text":"was this guy."},{"time":668143,"text":"And he gave a wonderful technical talk."},{"time":670743,"text":"He's a professor at MIT."},{"time":672342,"text":"But in essence what he said"},{"time":674258,"text":"is you can take retroviruses,"},{"time":675958,"text":"which get inside brain cells of mice."},{"time":678758,"text":"You can tag them with proteins"},{"time":681198,"text":"that light up when you light them."},{"time":683292,"text":"And you can map the exact pathways"},{"time":687008,"text":"when a mouse sees, feels, touches,"},{"time":690491,"text":"remembers, loves."},{"time":692674,"text":"And then you can take a fiber optic cable"},{"time":695047,"text":"and light up some of the same things."},{"time":698866,"text":"And by the way, as you do this,"},{"time":700698,"text":"you can image it in two colors,"},{"time":702715,"text":"which means you can download this information"},{"time":705114,"text":"as binary code directly into a computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709854,"text":"So what's the bottom line on that?"},{"time":712327,"text":"Well it's not completely inconceivable"},{"time":714527,"text":"that someday you'll be able to download your own memories,"},{"time":719022,"text":"maybe into a new body."},{"time":721409,"text":"And maybe you can upload other people's memories as well."},{"time":726494,"text":"And this might have just one or two"},{"time":729008,"text":"small ethical, political, moral implications."},{"time":732528,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":734059,"text":"Just a thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737050,"text":"Here's the kind of questions"},{"time":738578,"text":"that are becoming interesting questions"},{"time":740558,"text":"for philosophers, for governing people,"},{"time":743042,"text":"for economists, for scientists."},{"time":746408,"text":"Because these technologies are moving really quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749692,"text":"And as you think about it,"},{"time":751192,"text":"let me close with an example of the brain."},{"time":754274,"text":"The first place where you would expect"},{"time":755957,"text":"to see enormous evolutionary pressure today,"},{"time":759008,"text":"both because of the inputs,"},{"time":761273,"text":"which are becoming massive,"},{"time":762825,"text":"and because of the plasticity of the organ,"},{"time":764607,"text":"is the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767141,"text":"Do we have any evidence that that is happening?"},{"time":770459,"text":"Well let's take a look at something like autism incidence per thousand."},{"time":775190,"text":"Here's what it looks like in 2000."},{"time":777692,"text":"Here's what it looks like in 2002,"},{"time":779774,"text":"2006, 2008."},{"time":784392,"text":"Here's the increase in less than a decade."},{"time":788474,"text":"And we still don't know why this is happening."},{"time":792891,"text":"What we do know is, potentially,"},{"time":795376,"text":"the brain is reacting in"},{"time":797408,"text":"a hyperactive, hyper-plastic way,"},{"time":799542,"text":"and creating individuals that are like this."},{"time":802492,"text":"And this is only one of the conditions that's out there."},{"time":805249,"text":"You've also got people with who are extraordinarily smart,"},{"time":808789,"text":"people who can remember everything they've seen in their lives,"},{"time":811186,"text":"people who've got synesthesia,"},{"time":812571,"text":"people who've got schizophrenia."},{"time":813902,"text":"You've got all kinds of stuff going on out there,"},{"time":816436,"text":"and we still don't understand"},{"time":817654,"text":"how and why this is happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819887,"text":"But one question you might want to ask is,"},{"time":822569,"text":"are we seeing a rapid evolution of the brain"},{"time":825197,"text":"and of how we process data?"},{"time":827022,"text":"Because when you think of how much data's coming into our brains,"},{"time":830085,"text":"we're trying to take in as much data in a day"},{"time":833569,"text":"as people used to take in in a lifetime."},{"time":836120,"text":"And as you're thinking about this,"},{"time":838752,"text":"there's four theories as to why this might be going on,"},{"time":841094,"text":"plus a whole series of others."},{"time":842421,"text":"I don't have a good answer."},{"time":844070,"text":"There really needs to be more research on this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847686,"text":"One option is the fast food fetish."},{"time":849921,"text":"There's beginning to be some evidence"},{"time":852370,"text":"that obesity and diet"},{"time":854621,"text":"have something to do"},{"time":856252,"text":"with gene modifications,"},{"time":858020,"text":"which may or may not have an impact"},{"time":860370,"text":"on how the brain of an infant works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":863887,"text":"A second option is the sexy geek option."},{"time":867842,"text":"These conditions are highly rare."},{"time":872085,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":875123,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":880423,"text":"But what's beginning to happen"},{"time":882056,"text":"is because these geeks are all getting together,"},{"time":884590,"text":"because they are highly qualified for computer programming"},{"time":887487,"text":"and it is highly remunerated,"},{"time":889805,"text":"as well as other very detail-oriented tasks,"},{"time":892955,"text":"that they are concentrating geographically"},{"time":895404,"text":"and finding like-minded mates."},{"time":898371,"text":"So this is the assortative mating hypothesis"},{"time":901939,"text":"of these genes reinforcing one another"},{"time":904639,"text":"in these structures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906756,"text":"The third, is this too much information?"},{"time":909706,"text":"We're trying to process so much stuff"},{"time":911203,"text":"that some people get synesthetic"},{"time":913555,"text":"and just have huge pipes that remember everything."},{"time":916155,"text":"Other people get hyper-sensitive to the amount of information."},{"time":918824,"text":"Other people react with various psychological conditions"},{"time":922806,"text":"or reactions to this information."},{"time":924438,"text":"Or maybe it's chemicals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":927140,"text":"But when you see an increase"},{"time":928905,"text":"of that order of magnitude in a condition,"},{"time":931256,"text":"either you're not measuring it right"},{"time":932821,"text":"or there's something going on very quickly,"},{"time":935339,"text":"and it may be evolution in real time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939371,"text":"Here's the bottom line."},{"time":941874,"text":"What I think we are doing"},{"time":944055,"text":"is we're transitioning as a species."},{"time":945771,"text":"And I didn't think this when Steve Gullans and I started writing together."},{"time":951255,"text":"I think we're transitioning into Homo evolutis"},{"time":953706,"text":"that, for better or worse,"},{"time":955105,"text":"is not just a hominid that's conscious of his or her environment,"},{"time":959287,"text":"it's a hominid that's beginning to directly and deliberately"},{"time":962506,"text":"control the evolution of its own species,"},{"time":965704,"text":"of bacteria, of plants, of animals."},{"time":969538,"text":"And I think that's such an order of magnitude change"},{"time":972373,"text":"that your grandkids or your great-grandkids"},{"time":975476,"text":"may be a species very different from you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978521,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":980107,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}